race.comment: Competitive EMERALD COURT (7) is a leader who has been narrowly beaten at Colac at her two most recent outings. Hill takes over from the 3kg apprentice and he's likely to control the race. Well placed to return to the winners' list. MISSED THE MARK (1) is up to this but hasn't been enjoying much luck. He's been freshened 45 days and tumbles in grade off the latest. He's capable of using the inside barrier. BALGOWAN (9) resumes and is proven fresh. Won this grade/trip at Tatura last time and has a 2kg claim and an inside barrier. Likely to race well with the four jumpouts under the saddle. REDEMPTION TIME (6) improved just missing at Camperdown and has plenty of weight relief today with a 4kg claimer engaged. The gate is tricky. PLEASE ME DO (8) is hard to catch but has pieces of form that would see him very competitive. Better suited back to this level.
